section.text:
Gonorrhea - New Counseling done., Kayla Holloway is a 16 Years & 7 Months Old Female ( DOB 10/12/2003) presents to clinic for gonorrhea treatment. Labs done 05/22 positive for gonorrhea. Denies vaginal discharge, rash, dysuria or abdominal pain. Uses condoms. Pt on depo for birth control but states she does not want to take it again due to menstrual irregularities and wants to think about another option. , No, No, No, No, 05/22/2020, Done, Done, 06/22/2020, , Use fluoridated toothpaste. Brush in the morning after breakfast. Brush and floss after your final meal of the day. , 05/22/2020, DYSURIA - New ·Instructions: Borderline urine with 1+ Leu and blood. Will start on antibiotic treatment for 5 days and send urine for culture., Screening, STI - New ·Instructions: Will call with results STI screening sent. Had HIV testing in the last year., Ankle joint pain, right - New ·Instructions: Fracture unlikely given bearing weight and location of pain. Discussed supportive care and when to return, No rashes, no abnormal lesions , no accessory muscle use, no retractions, lungs clear to auscultation bilaterally, symmetric air movement, Kayla Holloway is a 16 Years & 7 Months Old Female ( DOB 10/12/2003) here for ankle pain and STD check. She says she thinks she rolled her ankle about 2 days ago. She has been able to walk on it. She tried ice which only helped a little. She has not tried any medicines. The pain is located on the outside of her right ankle. She has not noticed any swelling. There is pain when she is inverting the ankle. She says outside of this, she always seems to have some pain in her ankle.
She also would like to be screened for STI. Last sexual intercouse was 2 weeks ago. She says she used protection (and always does). She says she started to develop dyusiria about 2 days ago with some lower abdominal pain. She has no discharge.
At end of visit, patient asked if clinic did "rape kits." Asked patient why she was asking and she said she was just curious. Asked whether anything had happened, she said no. She said she had nothing that she wanted to talk about. She made no disclosures., Yes, No, No, Yes, Yes
